# ⚠️ DO NOT DEPLOY THIS CSP UNTIL THE SELF-HOSTED ASSETS ARE ACTIVE (SELF-HOST.md).
# It is intentionally NOT wired up yet: the shipped build still loads the NER model
# from the Hugging Face CDN (names.ts `allowRemoteModels = true`), which this
# `connect-src 'self'` policy would BLOCK — breaking name detection in production.
# Activate only after: model in R2 + served same-origin, names.ts/ocr.ts pointed at
# local paths (allowRemoteModels=false). This file is committed as prep, inert until
# the site is actually deployed via the SELF-HOST.md sequence.
#
# Cloudflare Pages response headers. The CSP is the ENFORCEMENT of the product's
# core promise: default-src 'self' + connect-src 'self' means the browser will
# refuse any outbound request to a third party — your client documents physically
# cannot leave this origin. The detection model, ONNX-runtime WASM, and tesseract
# assets are all served from this origin (see SELF-HOST.md), so nothing here needs
# an external host. 'wasm-unsafe-eval' is required to compile the WASM detection
# engines; worker-src blob: is for the tesseract/pdf.js web workers.
#
# NOTE: applied on the deployed site only, not in `vite dev` (Vite's HMR client
# needs looser script rules). Verify no-egress in dev by watching the network panel.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'wasm-unsafe-eval'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; worker-src 'self' blob:; child-src 'self' blob:; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
